Capturing user input

we need to add three elements to capture user input:


add an input widget - like radioButtons() above your tableOutput in the UI. You’ll need to comma-splice that - all your UI contents gets joined with commas
then add an input ID to that input widget radioButtons("my_input", "Which gear to show?", sort(unique(mtcars$gear)))

finally, you connect your user input into your code using input$my_input



ui &lt;- fluidPage(
  radioButtons("my_input", "Which gear to show?", sort(unique(mtcars$gear))),
  tableOutput("my_table")
)

server &lt;- function(input, output, session) {
  output$my_table &lt;- renderTable(mtcars |&gt;
                dplyr::filter(gear == input$my_input) |&gt;
                dplyr::group_by(cyl) |&gt;
                dplyr::summarise(mpg = round(mean(mpg), 2)))
}

